    <subsection xml:id="pattern-rules">
        <title>Describing Rules in Words and Algebra</title>
        <p>
        Once we recognize a pattern, we can describe it using words or algebraic expressions.
        </p>

        <example>
        <title>Rule from a Pattern</title>
        <p>
            Given the pattern <m>4, 7, 10, 13, ...</m>, describe the rule and write an expression for the <m>n</m>th term.
        </p>
        <p>Each term increases by 3. First term is 4.</p>
        <p><m>n</m>th term: <m>3n + 1</m></p>
        </example>

        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>Find a rule and an expression for the <m>n</m>th term of the pattern: <m>2, 6, 10, 14, ...</m></p>
            </statement>
        </exercise>

        <figure>
        <caption>Graphical representation of a pattern and its algebraic rule.</caption>
        <image source="images/nth-term-pattern.svg" width="60%" />
        </figure>
    </subsection>